com.ikalagaming.plugins

Enum PluginState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<PluginState>
      • com.ikalagaming.plugins.PluginState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<PluginState>

    public enum PluginState
extends java.lang.Enum<PluginState>
    The plugin state is a simple way of determining what a plugin is doing and whether or not it can be interacted with or perform tasks. When each value should be used is described in the appropriate Plugin methods.
    These values do not strictly have to be set as suggested, but it is optimal if they are as changing the flow of how a plugin is operated will likely cause problems.
    Author:
    Ches Burks

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • LOADING

        public static final PluginState LOADING
        The plugin is being loaded and is not yet in memory fully. It is not able to be usable yet. Related files are likely locked and some basic data is being loaded into memory.

      • UNLOADING

        public static final PluginState UNLOADING
        The plugin is being unloaded from memory but is still partially loaded. It is not able to be used, but related files are likely still locked and the plugins data likely still exists in memory.

      • ENABLING

        public static final PluginState ENABLING
        The plugin is being enabled but has not completed the process. It is not guaranteed to be usable yet.

      • DISABLING

        public static final PluginState DISABLING
        The plugin is disabling itself but has not completed the process. It is not likely to still be usable.

      • ENABLED

        public static final PluginState ENABLED
        The plugin is fully enabled and running. It can be used at this point.

      • DISABLED

        public static final PluginState DISABLED
        The plugin is fully disabled but still loaded in memory. It is not able to be used.

      • PENDING_REMOVAL

        public static final PluginState PENDING_REMOVAL
        The plugin has unloaded itself as much as reasonable. This is a value used to indicate that it is no longer in use and further removal is to be done outside of the plugin.

      • CORRUPTED

        public static final PluginState CORRUPTED
        There was a problem and the plugin is now in an unstable state. It may be partially loaded/enabled or unloaded/disabled. The system will attempt to fix the problem, but if it cannot then the plugin will be removed.

      • NOT_LOADED

        public static final PluginState NOT_LOADED
        The plugin does not exist as far as the manager is concerned. If the plugin state of a non-existent plugin is requested, this is the value that is returned.

      • DISCOVERED

        public static final PluginState DISCOVERED
        The plugin has been discovered, which means the system found it in a file, has loaded data about it, but has yet to check dependencies or start loading it up.

      • DEPS_CHECKING

        public static final PluginState DEPS_CHECKING
        The system is checking dependencies for the plugin, but has not determined whether or not dependencies are satisfied.

      • DEPS_SATISFIED

        public static final PluginState DEPS_SATISFIED
        The system has checked for dependencies, and confirmed that all dependencies are satisfied. A plugin with no dependencies has all dependencies satisfied. A plugin with all dependencies either being loaded simultaneously or having been loaded previously also has its dependencies satisfied.

      • DEPS_MISSING

        public static final PluginState DEPS_MISSING
        The plugin has dependencies which no currently loaded plugin, or plugin loaded simultaneously, satisfies. This will be reported and unloaded.
